<Link id="l00902" /><CodeLine lineNumber="902"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// The concept of the reassociation pass is that these operations can benefit</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00903" /><CodeLine lineNumber="903"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// from this kind of transformation:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00904" /><CodeLine lineNumber="904"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00905" /><CodeLine lineNumber="905"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A = ? op ?</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00906" /><CodeLine lineNumber="906"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// B = A op X (Prev)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00907" /><CodeLine lineNumber="907"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// C = B op Y (Root)</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00908" /><CodeLine lineNumber="908"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// --&gt;</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00909" /><CodeLine lineNumber="909"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// A = ? op ?</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00910" /><CodeLine lineNumber="910"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// B = X op Y</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00911" /><CodeLine lineNumber="911"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// C = A op B</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00912" /><CodeLine lineNumber="912"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00913" /><CodeLine lineNumber="913"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// breaking the dependency between A and B, allowing them to be executed in</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00914" /><CodeLine lineNumber="914"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// parallel (or back-to-back in a pipeline) instead of depending on each other.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00915" /><CodeLine lineNumber="915"></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00916" /><CodeLine lineNumber="916"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// FIXME: This has the potential to be expensive (compile time) while not</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00917" /><CodeLine lineNumber="917"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// improving the code at all. Some ways to limit the overhead:</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00918" /><CodeLine lineNumber="918"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 1 Track successful transforms; bail out if hit rate gets too low.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00919" /><CodeLine lineNumber="919"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 2 Only enable at -O3 or some other non-default optimization level.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00920" /><CodeLine lineNumber="920"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">// 3 Pre-screen pattern candidates here: if an operand of the previous</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00921" /><CodeLine lineNumber="921"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    instruction is known to not increase the critical path, then don&#39;t match</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00922" /><CodeLine lineNumber="922"><span class="doxyHighlightComment">//    that pattern.</span></CodeLine>
<Link id="l00923" /><CodeLine lineNumber="923" lineLink="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetinstrinfo/#a861381cad67866e249c6330631ac0742"><span class="doxyHighlightKeywordType">bool</span><span class="doxyHighlight"> <a href="/docs/api/classes/llvm/targetinstrinfo/#a861381cad67866e249c6330631ac0742">TargetInstrInfo::getMachineCombinerPatterns</a>(</span></CodeLine>
